text: 304 is a number. It comes after 303 and before 305. == In mathematics == * 304 is an even number. * It is a composite number, meaning it has more than two factors. * The prime factorization of 304 is: 304 = 2⁴ × 19 (which means 2 × 2 × 2 × 2 × 19) * The digits of 304 add up to 7 (3 + 0 + 4 = 7). * 304 is an example of a number that is divisible by 16 (because it has 2⁴ in its factors). == In other areas == * HTTP 304 is a status code on the internet, meaning "Not Modified" — the requested web page has not changed4 * Halloween is on the 304th day of every common year (305th day in leap years)
title: 304 (number)
